sections.text:
4.1 It is recommended that the production and issuance of the certificates for fish and fishery products should be carried out in accordance with the principles and appropriate sections of the:
• Guidelines for Generic Official Certificate Formats and the Production and Issuance of Certificates (CAC/GL 38-2001);
• Principles for Food Import and Export Inspection And Certification (CAC/GL 20-1995);
• Guidelines for the Design, Operation, Assessment and Accreditation of Food Import and Export Inspection and Certification Systems (CAC/GL 26-1997);
• Guidelines for the Development of Equivalence Agreements Regarding Food Import and Export Inspection and Certification Systems (CAC/GL 34-1999);
• Proposed Draft Revised Code of Ethics for International Trade in Foods (under revision by the CCGP).
4.2 The selection of the appropriate language(s) of certificates should be based on adequacy for the importing country’s purpose, comprehension by the certifying officer and minimizing unnecessary burden on the exporting country.

